By                     
                                    MICHAEL KOLOMATSKY
                            
                FEB. 1, 2018
    
The five most-viewed listings on The New York Times’s “Find a Home” site last month included a modern house in Colorado with vast indoor and outdoor spaces and a 10-bedroom bed-and-breakfast in the Pocono Mountains.
1
$9,500,000
3 Countryside Lane
Cherry Hills Village, Colo.
The most viewed listing in January was a modern house about 20 minutes south of Denver, with four bedrooms and 10,070 square feet of living space. Sliding glass walls extend the home’s indoor space out into the two-and-a-half-acre property.
Broker LIV Sotheby’s International Realty
2
$1,449,999
1 Coach Road
Bear Creek, Pa. 
The Bischwind, a Pocono Mountains bed-and-breakfast with 10 bedrooms, a 60-person event space, a terrace and a pool was the second most viewed. According to the listing, President William Taft was once a guest at the 19th-century house.
Broker Kurfiss Sotheby’s International Realty
3
$799,500
6008 N Landis Avenue
Sea Isle City, N.J.
Next, a four-bedroom townhouse on the Jersey Shore. With three levels, two decks and good parking, it has rental potential and plenty of space for entertaining. The house is about an hour and a half from Philadelphia and two and a half hours from New York.
Broker Landis Company
4
$999,000
170 East 78th Street, No. 3C
Upper East Side
Fourth most viewed was a refined-looking one-bedroom in a prewar co-op. But the home’s 16-by-29-foot living room, large windows, 13-foot ceilings and washer/dryer come with a steep monthly maintenance of $2,980. Pieds-à-terre and pets are allowed.
Broker Brown Harris Stevens
5
$749,000
360 West 21st Street, No. 5L
Chelsea
Finally, a one-bedroom prewar co-op drew a lot of interest. The compact renovated apartment has a kitchen with Caesarstone counters and a bathroom with Italian porcelain tile, a walk-in shower and new floors.
Broker Brown Harris Stevens
